<item>
            <title>[LU-299] Uninitialized variable in shrinker test makes it fail incorrectly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-299</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Commit 6697349ea92c2c61a40b8f23655f66de60ca1501 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-73&quot; title=&quot;RHEL6 kernel support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-73&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-73&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a minor regression in the LC_SHRINKER_WANT_SHRINK_PTR test for pre-RHEL6.1.  Use of the uninitialized variable &quot;struct shrinker tmp&quot; is flagged as an error, making the test fail erroneously.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will submit a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>pre-RHEL6.1</environment>
